description:
Dalmatian toadflax plant found to be around 0.5 metres tall, growing straight upright. Flowers are yellow, contain a short hypanthium, 5 sepals, and a long spur petal on the underside. The inside is tinged orange and has a hirsute texture.
Leaves thick and rubbery, alternate, and cordate, clasping the stem.

Mullein growing in shrub-step landscape amongst dry grasses with several other mullein nearby. Height around 1.6 metres with the upper part in fruit and lower down yellow flowers were forming in clusters above each leaf. Leaves entire, sessile, around 7-30cm. Both stem and leaves are tomentose, leaves having dense hairs on both sides and pinnate venation.
Flowers having 5 yellow petals and light green sepals with dense hairs inside corolla.
This observation refers to the lower of the two weevils.
Frequent in park
Squaw currant or whisky currant
Habrotat shots at end. H. hirsutus also found in area
